I&#39;m not 100% familiar with Boost.MPL, but this should do what you&#39;re looking for:

    template &lt;class Variant&gt;
    struct mpl_types_impl;
    
    template &lt;class... Ts&gt;
    struct mpl_types_impl&lt;std::variant&lt;Ts...&gt;&gt; {
    	using type = boost::mpl::vector&lt;Ts...&gt;;
    };
    
    template &lt;class Variant&gt;
    using mpl_types = typename mpl_types_impl&lt;Variant&gt;::type;

[See it live on Wandbox](https://wandbox.org/permlink/0aYgTemKwhZbjwRY)

It looks like there is a way, using the [AntiXSS library](https://www.nuget.org/packages/AntiXSS/) which was announced to be [End of life](https://archive.codeplex.com/?p=wpl) (except for security fixes if needed).

So it isn&#39;t deprecated or obsolete, just no longer very actively maintained because parts that Microsoft considered essential have been ported into .NET Framework v4.0. And it looks they did not port the part that we need here.

